at they are impossible) to improve for melee classes. <br><br>ARMOR PENALTY: Again, this is one of those that trivializes towards the latter stages of the gamer's career. The AC bonus would be great early on, but negligible in the end.<br><br>VISION: I agree with Rexz on this. Relying on spells is no big deal. You'd have to be lazy to consider a few clicks a hassle.<br><br>SWIMMING: Again, trivial for people who do not fight underwater. Still it is a very easy skill to build up. Simply auto-run towards a corner of a pool. Look up. Leave it on for the night, and presto.<br><br>GNOMES: I won't bother with this because quite frank, they look ridiculous enough. :)<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=680092 target=_new>Adiemus Aeternum</a>, <a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=724036 target=_new>Gaoler Loudbottom</a> - Firiona Vie</td></td></tr>
